-- Colombian Stock Movers: ETB, Canacol, Pacific Rubiales
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-05-08T20:53:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-08/colombian-stock-movers-etb-ecopetrol-canacol-are-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  fell 0.4 percent to 15,187.15, while the
 Colcap Index (COLCAP)  decreased 0.3 percent to 1,796.45.  Empresa de Telecomunicaciones de Bogota SA  (ETB CB), the
phone company serving  Colombia ’s capital, dropped 1.4 percent to
506 pesos. ETB said in a filing to the financial regulator that
it would propose at a shareholder meeting tomorrow taking on as
much as $600 million in debt.  Oil producers dropped as crude for June delivery fell for a
fifth day in  New York .  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)  , a Toronto-based
oil producer that operates fields in Colombia, decreased 0.5
percent to 50,160 pesos.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNE)  , the Calgary-based  oil
company  that operates fields in Colombia, slumped 3.1 percent to
1,260 pesos.  Ecopetrol SA (EC)  , Colombia’s largest oil company,
was unchanged at 5,650 pesos after earlier dropping as much as
2.1 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Christine Jenkins in New York at 
